quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  25,12,"When it sees them from a far place, they will hear the (furious) raging and the groaning it has"
  25,13,"And when they are cast in a strait place thereof, interlinked, they will call there for detriment (s). \"Do not call today for one detriment"
  25,14,and call for many destructions
  25,15,(rather) the Garden of Eternity that is promised to the pious? It is for them a recompense and a Destiny
  25,16,"promise upon your Lord, of Him to be asked (by His righteous bondmen)"
  25,17,"Allah, then He will say, \"Was it you who led these My bondmen into error, or did they themselves err away from the way"
  25,18,selves any patrons apart from You; but You gave them and their fathers enjoyment until they forgot the Remembrance and were a spoiled people
  25,19,"able either to turn it about or vindicate (yourselves). And whoever of you does injustice, We will make him taste a great torment"
  25,20,"indeed ate food and walked in the markets. And We have made some of you to be a temptation for (some) others. \"Will you (endure) patiently?\" And your Lord has been Ever-Beholding"